A third-party committee formed by
Universal Entertainment says no evidence to show the company has
paid $40 million in bribery payments in  Philippines , the
Japanese company says in a stock exchange statement today.
* Committee members include former Japan National Police Agency
official and two lawyers, co. has said. {NXTW NSN MGEJ1J6K50Y8
